# Feedback API Tests
# Use with VS Code REST Client or IntelliJ HTTP Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5147

### Submit Feedback - Bug Report
# Report a bug with all required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "bug",
  "email": "tester@example.com",
  "message": "Found an issue when masking SSN numbers with hyphens. The mask format doesn't match the original structure.",
  "name": "Test User",
  "rating": 4,
  "subject": "SSN masking format issue",
  "wantsReply": true
}

### Submit Feedback - Feature Request
# Request a new feature
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "feature",
  "email": "developer@example.com",
  "message": "Would love to see support for custom masking patterns that I can define myself.",
  "name": "Developer",
  "rating": 5,
  "subject": "Custom masking patterns",
  "wantsReply": false
}

### Submit Feedback - Minimal (no optional fields)
# Submit with only required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "general",
  "message": "Great tool for privacy protection!"
}

### Submit Feedback - Invalid Category
# Should return validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "invalid-category",
  "message": "This should fail validation"
}

### Submit Feedback - Missing Message
# Should return validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "bug",
  "message": ""
}

### Submit Feedback - Invalid Email Format
# Should return validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/feedback
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "bug",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "message": "Test message with invalid email"
}
